This paper focuses on facial action unit detection using deep learning techniques, which falls under computer vision (cs.CV) and machine learning (cs.LG) sub-categories. The paper also discusses the use of Long Short-Term Memory (LSTM) networks, which are commonly used in natural language processing (NLP) and sequential data analysis, making cs.AI a likely sub-category as well. Additionally, the paper deals with the analysis of facial expressions, which is relevant to multimedia (cs.MM) and human-computer interaction (cs.HC) sub-categories.
